title: A DWBA analysis of C-12(d,pg)C-13 with measured optical model parameters.

x4freetext: A DWBA analysis of C-12(d,pg)C-13 with measured optical
model parameters.

x4codes.hlp: Duke University, Durham, NC, United States of America
Duke University, Durham, NC, United States of America

x4freetext: The 4 MeV Van de Graaff accelerator was
used.
The 12C+d yield curves and the elastic scattering were
measured with a 30.5 cm diam. scattering chamber
designed for use with solid state counters. The chamber
was made of aluminium and has an internal diameter and
depth of 30.5 cm and 7.6 cm, respectively. Detector
mounts could be placed in any of six equally spaced
slots cut in each scattering table and their distances
from the target were adjustable.

x4freetext: The 300 mu-m surface barrier detectors were used
The self-supporting carbon target was approximately
17 keV thick for 1.9 MeV protons.
The absolute cross section error. Sources
of uncertainty were scattering angle inaccuracies,
finite detection apertures, bombarding energy
fluctuations, changes in target thickness, counting
statistics, inaccuracies in dead time corrections,
incorrect current integration and background
subtraction.
